@@yMUD CLIENTS@@N

Using a dedicated MUD client is strongly recommended.  It gives you
features like triggers, aliases, macros, scrollback, and proper color
rendering that a plain telnet session cannot match.

Popular free options:
  @@cMUSHclient@@N  — Windows, highly scriptable
  @@cTintin++@@N   — Linux/Mac/Windows, lightweight
  @@cMudlet@@N     — cross-platform, active development

@@yColor Note:@@N

ACK!TNG uses ANSI color codes.  Make sure your client has color enabled
and is set to use the standard 16-color ANSI palette.  Some clients
default to a "bright" scheme that swaps colors — switch to "normal" or
"dim" if colors look wrong.
